article.headline: Georgia 74, Wofford 73
article.story: ATHENS, Ga. -- Zac Swansey made a game-winning 3-pointer at the buzzer to lift Georgia to a 74-73 overtime victory over Wofford on Saturday. Swansey hit a shot with 14.7 seconds to play to tie the score at 71-71, but Wofford's Brad Loesing raced down the floor to make a layup with 5.8 seconds to play to give the Terriers a lead. Trey Thompkins threw the inbounds pass away, forcing Georgia to foul. The Bulldogs put Tim Johnson on the line, and he missed both shots. This time Swansey got the outlet pass cleanly and hit the game winner. Thompkins led Georgia (7-3) with 15 points. Junior Salters led Wofford (4-4) with 20 points.
